The paper deals with the smoothing parameter of a Euclidean lattice, which is a fundamental concept in lattice-based cryptography and worst-case/average-case reductions for lattice problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG) which often involves the use of lattices.
